For 150 locations, **clustering isn't the right solution** — your colleague's suggestion would actually hurt performance and UX. Here's why and what to do instead:

## The Right Strategy: Symbol Layer

At 150 locations, you're in the "performance dead zone" for HTML Markers. Each `new mapboxgl.Marker()` creates a real DOM element, so you have 150+ nodes the browser must layout/paint every frame. But 150 isn't enough to warrant clustering (which is for 1,000+ locations).

**Switch to a Symbol Layer** — this renders all markers on the GPU via WebGL with zero DOM elements:

```javascript
map.on('load', () => {
  // Add your GeoJSON as a source
  map.addSource('coffee-shops', {
    type: 'geojson',
    data: yourCoffeeShopsGeoJSON
  });

  // Load custom coffee icon
  map.loadImage('/coffee-marker.png', (error, image) => {
    if (error) throw error;
    map.addImage('coffee-marker', image);

    // Add symbol layer - renders on GPU, not DOM
    map.addLayer({
      id: 'coffee-shops-layer',
      type: 'symbol',
      source: 'coffee-shops',
      layout: {
        'icon-image': 'coffee-marker',
        'icon-size': 0.8,
        'icon-allow-overlap': true,
        'text-field': ['get', 'name'],
        'text-font': ['Open Sans Bold', 'Arial Unicode MS Bold'],
        'text-offset': [0, 1.5],
        'text-anchor': 'top',
        'text-size': 12
      }
    });
  });

  // Handle clicks with Interactions API (recommended)
  map.addInteraction('coffee-click', {
    type: 'click',
    target: { layerId: 'coffee-shops-layer' },
    handler: (e) => {
      const shop = e.features[0];
      showCoffeeShopDetails(shop);
    }
  });

  // Or traditional event listener:
  // map.on('click', 'coffee-shops-layer', (e) => {
  //   const shop = e.features[0];
  //   showCoffeeShopDetails(shop);
  // });

  // Cursor changes
  map.on('mouseenter', 'coffee-shops-layer', () => {
    map.getCanvas().style.cursor = 'pointer';
  });

  map.on('mouseleave', 'coffee-shops-layer', () => {
    map.getCanvas().style.cursor = '';
  });
});

function showCoffeeShopDetails(shop) {
  // Fly to location
  map.flyTo({
    center: shop.geometry.coordinates,
    zoom: 15
  });

  // Show popup
  new mapboxgl.Popup()
    .setLngLat(shop.geometry.coordinates)
    .setHTML(`
      <h3>${shop.properties.name}</h3>
      <p>${shop.properties.address}</p>
      <p>${shop.properties.hours || ''}</p>
    `)
    .addTo(map);
}
```

## Why Not Clustering?

Clustering is for **visual decluttering** at 1,000+ locations, not performance optimization at 150. With only 150 coffee shops:

- **Bad UX**: Users lose the ability to see individual locations at medium zoom levels
- **Extra complexity**: Cluster click handlers, zoom-to-expand logic, count labels
- **Still slow**: You'd still need HTML Markers or Symbol Layers for unclustered points

## Performance Comparison

| Strategy | DOM Elements | Render Method | Best For |
|---|---|---|---|
| 150 HTML Markers | 150 | DOM layout/paint | ❌ Too slow |
| Symbol Layer | 1 (`<canvas>`) | GPU/WebGL | ✅ **Perfect for 150** |
| Clustering | Varies | Complex | ❌ Overkill |

## Migration from HTML Markers

If you need to keep some HTML Marker functionality, you can combine approaches:

```javascript
// Symbol layer for performance
map.addLayer({
  id: 'coffee-shops',
  type: 'symbol',
  source: 'coffee-shops',
  layout: {
    'icon-image': 'coffee-marker',
    'icon-size': 0.8
  }
});

// Add HTML marker only for selected shop (when needed)
let selectedMarker = null;

function highlightSelected(shop) {
  // Remove previous selected marker
  if (selectedMarker) {
    selectedMarker.remove();
  }

  // Add special HTML marker for selected shop
  const el = document.createElement('div');
  el.className = 'selected-coffee-marker';

  selectedMarker = new mapboxgl.Marker(el)
    .setLngLat(shop.geometry.coordinates)
    .addTo(map);
}
```

**Bottom line**: Switch to Symbol Layer. Your page will be smooth again, and you'll avoid the complexity of clustering that you don't actually need.

**Don't call the API directly with fetch()!** There's a much better approach for your use case.

## Recommended: Search JS Core + Custom UI

Use **Mapbox Search JS Core** instead of direct API calls. It handles all the complex parts (session tokens, debouncing, race conditions) while giving you complete control over the UI.

Here's why Search JS Core is perfect for your needs:

✅ **Complete UI control** - No pre-built components, build exactly what you want  
✅ **Automatic session token management** - No manual token generation/tracking  
✅ **Built-in debouncing** - No need to implement your own  
✅ **Race condition handling** - Later requests don't overwrite newer ones  
✅ **Production-ready** - Used by Mapbox internally  

## Complete Implementation

**Installation:**
```bash
npm install @mapbox/search-js-core
```

**Full custom autocomplete with keyboard navigation:**

```javascript
import { SearchSession } from '@mapbox/search-js-core';

class CustomSearchAutocomplete {
  constructor(inputElement, resultsElement, options = {}) {
    this.input = inputElement;
    this.results = resultsElement;
    this.selectedIndex = -1;
    this.currentResults = [];

    // Search JS Core handles session tokens automatically
    this.search = new SearchSession({
      accessToken: options.accessToken
    });

    this.searchOptions = {
      country: options.country,
      types: options.types || 'address,poi',
      limit: options.limit || 8
    };

    this.setupEventListeners();
  }

  setupEventListeners() {
    // Handle typing
    this.input.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
      this.performSearch(e.target.value);
    });

    // Handle keyboard navigation
    this.input.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      this.handleKeyDown(e);
    });

    // Hide results when clicking outside
    document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      if (!this.input.contains(e.target) && !this.results.contains(e.target)) {
        this.hideResults();
      }
    });
  }

  async performSearch(query) {
    if (!query || query.length < 2) {
      this.hideResults();
      return;
    }

    try {
      // Search JS Core handles debouncing and session tokens automatically
      const response = await this.search.suggest(query, this.searchOptions);
      this.currentResults = response.suggestions || [];
      this.renderResults();
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Search error:', error);
      this.hideResults();
    }
  }

  renderResults() {
    if (this.currentResults.length === 0) {
      this.results.innerHTML = '<div class="no-results">No results found</div>';
      this.results.style.display = 'block';
      return;
    }

    // Your completely custom rendering
    this.results.innerHTML = this.currentResults.map((result, index) => `
      <div class="search-result ${index === this.selectedIndex ? 'selected' : ''}" 
           data-index="${index}">
        <div class="result-icon">${this.getResultIcon(result.feature_type)}</div>
        <div class="result-content">
          <div class="result-name">${result.name}</div>
          <div class="result-address">${result.place_formatted || ''}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-type">${result.feature_type}</div>
      </div>
    `).join('');

    // Add click handlers
    this.results.querySelectorAll('.search-result').forEach((el, index) => {
      el.addEventListener('click', () => this.selectResult(index));
    });

    this.results.style.display = 'block';
    this.selectedIndex = -1;
  }

  handleKeyDown(e) {
    if (!this.currentResults.length) return;

    switch (e.key) {
      case 'ArrowDown':
        e.preventDefault();
        this.selectedIndex = Math.min(this.selectedIndex + 1, this.currentResults.length - 1);
        this.updateSelection();
        break;

      case 'ArrowUp':
        e.preventDefault();
        this.selectedIndex = Math.max(this.selectedIndex - 1, -1);
        this.updateSelection();
        break;

      case 'Enter':
        e.preventDefault();
        if (this.selectedIndex >= 0) {
          this.selectResult(this.selectedIndex);
        }
        break;

      case 'Escape':
        this.hideResults();
        break;
    }
  }

  updateSelection() {
    // Update visual selection
    this.results.querySelectorAll('.search-result').forEach((el, index) => {
      el.classList.toggle('selected', index === this.selectedIndex);
    });

    // Scroll selected item into view
    if (this.selectedIndex >= 0) {
      const selectedEl = this.results.children[this.selectedIndex];
      selectedEl.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest' });
    }
  }

  async selectResult(index) {
    const suggestion = this.currentResults[index];

    try {
      // Retrieve full details (Search JS Core handles session tokens)
      const result = await this.search.retrieve(suggestion);
      const feature = result.features[0];

      // Update input
      this.input.value = feature.properties.name;
      this.hideResults();

      // Trigger custom event with full feature data
      this.input.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('search-select', {
        detail: { feature, suggestion }
      }));

    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Retrieve error:', error);
    }
  }

  hideResults() {
    this.results.style.display = 'none';
    this.currentResults = [];
    this.selectedIndex = -1;
  }

  getResultIcon(type) {
    const icons = {
      'poi': '📍',
      'address': '🏠',
      'place': '📌',
      'postcode': '📮'
    };
    return icons[type] || '📍';
  }
}

// Usage
const autocomplete = new CustomSearchAutocomplete(
  document.getElementById('search-input'),
  document.getElementById('search-results'),
  {
    accessToken: 'YOUR_MAPBOX_TOKEN',
    country: 'US', // Optional
    types: 'address,poi'
  }
);

// Handle selection
document.getElementById('search-input').addEventListener('search-select', (e) => {
  const { feature } = e.detail;
  const [lng, lat] = feature.geometry.coordinates;

  // Do whatever you want with the result
  console.log('Selected:', feature.properties.name);
  console.log('Coordinates:', lng, lat);

  // Fly map, add marker, etc.
});
```

