## Complete Working Example

```javascript
import mapboxgl from 'mapbox-gl';
import 'mapbox-gl/dist/mapbox-gl.css';

// Set token (use environment variable in production)
mapboxgl.accessToken = import.meta.env.VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN || 'pk.your_token_here';

// Now create your map
const map = new mapboxgl.Map({
  container: 'map',
  style: 'mapbox://styles/mapbox/streets-v12',
  center: [-122.4194, 37.7749],
  zoom: 12
});

// All your existing MapLibre code works unchanged
map.on('load', () => {
  new mapboxgl.Marker()
    .setLngLat([-122.4194, 37.7749])
    .addTo(map);
});
```

**Key point:** This is the main difference between MapLibre and Mapbox. MapLibre doesn't require a token (uses OSM tiles), but Mapbox requires a token to access their premium vector tiles and services.

The token gives you access to Mapbox's high-quality maps, satellite imagery, and ecosystem. The free tier includes 50,000 map loads per month, which is generous for most applications.

For your real-time fleet tracking use case, you need to be strategic about tool selection due to the high frequency of operations. Let me break down the optimal approach:

## The Performance Reality

**Your volume:** 50 trucks × 30 checks/minute = 1,500 containment checks per minute

At this frequency, using MCP tools over the network for every containment check would add significant latency due to:
- Network round-trip time
- AI agent reasoning overhead for each call
- Serialization/deserialization of coordinates

## Recommended Hybrid Architecture

### For Hot Path (Real-time Geofencing):
Use **Turf.js directly in-process** for the containment checks:

```javascript
import * as turf from '@turf/turf';

// Pre-load your restricted zones once
const restrictedZones = loadGeoJSONPolygons();

// For each truck position update (every 2 seconds)
function checkTruckPosition(truckId, newPosition) {
  for (const zone of restrictedZones) {
    const isInside = turf.booleanPointInPolygon(newPosition, zone);

    // Track state changes
    if (isInside && !previousState[truckId][zone.id]) {
      // Truck entered zone
      handleZoneEntry(truckId, zone.id);
    } else if (!isInside && previousState[truckId][zone.id]) {
      // Truck left zone
      handleZoneExit(truckId, zone.id);
    }
  }
}
```

### For Peripheral Operations (Use MCP Tools):

**Zone Management:**
```javascript
// Create new restricted zones based on travel time
const deliveryZone = await mapbox.isochrone_tool({
  coordinates: { longitude: depotLng, latitude: depotLat },
  contours_minutes: [30],
  profile: "mapbox/driving"
});

// Simplify complex zone boundaries for faster containment checks
const simplifiedZone = await mapbox.simplify_tool({
  geometry: complexBoundary,
  tolerance: 0.001,
  high_quality: false
});
```

**Route Planning & Optimization:**
```javascript
// When truck enters restricted zone, calculate fastest exit route
const exitRoute = await mapbox.directions_tool({
  coordinates: [
    { longitude: truckLng, latitude: truckLat },
    { longitude: exitPointLng, latitude: exitPointLat }
  ],
  routing_profile: 'mapbox/driving-traffic'
});

// Optimize routes for trucks that need rerouting
const optimizedRoute = await mapbox.optimization_tool({
  coordinates: trucksNeedingReroute,
  routing_profile: 'mapbox/driving-traffic'
});
```

**Visualization & Monitoring:**
```javascript
// Generate real-time fleet map
const fleetMap = await mapbox.static_map_image_tool({
  center: { longitude: centerLng, latitude: centerLat },
  zoom: 10,
  overlays: [
    ...restrictedZones.map(zone => ({ type: 'polygon', coordinates: zone.geometry.coordinates })),
    ...trucks.map(truck => ({ type: 'marker', coordinates: truck.position }))
  ]
});
```

## Complete Implementation Pattern

```javascript
class FleetTracker {
  constructor() {
    this.restrictedZones = [];
    this.truckStates = {}; // Track which zones each truck is in
  }

  // Setup: Use MCP to define zones
  async addRestrictedZone(description, centerPoint, travelMinutes) {
    const zone = await mapbox.isochrone_tool({
      coordinates: centerPoint,
      contours_minutes: [travelMinutes],
      profile: "mapbox/driving"
    });

    // Simplify for faster containment checks
    const simplified = await mapbox.simplify_tool({
      geometry: zone.features[0].geometry,
      tolerance: 0.0001
    });

    this.restrictedZones.push({
      id: Date.now(),
      description,
      geometry: simplified.geometry
    });
  }

  // Real-time: Use Turf.js directly
  processGPSUpdate(truckId, position) {
    if (!this.truckStates[truckId]) {
      this.truckStates[truckId] = {};
    }

    for (const zone of this.restrictedZones) {
      const isInside = turf.booleanPointInPolygon(position, zone.geometry);
      const wasInside = this.truckStates[truckId][zone.id] || false;

      if (isInside && !wasInside) {
        this.handleZoneEntry(truckId, zone.id, position);
      } else if (!isInside && wasInside) {
        this.handleZoneExit(truckId, zone.id, position);
      }

      this.truckStates[truckId][zone.id] = isInside;
    }
  }

  // Response: Use MCP for routing
  async handleZoneEntry(truckId, zoneId, position) {
    console.log(`Truck ${truckId} entered restricted zone ${zoneId}`);

    // Calculate fastest route out of zone
    const exitRoute = await mapbox.directions_tool({
      coordinates: [
        position,
        this.getNearestExitPoint(zoneId, position)
      ],
      routing_profile: 'mapbox/driving-traffic'
    });

    this.sendAlertToDriver(truckId, exitRoute);
  }
}
```

## When to Use MCP Tools vs Direct Turf.js

| Operation | Frequency | Use | Reason |
|-----------|-----------|-----|---------|
| **Containment checks** | Every 2 seconds | Direct Turf.js | High frequency, pure geometry |
| **Zone creation** | Once/rare | MCP `isochrone_tool` | Need routing for travel-time zones |
| **Zone simplification** | Once per zone | MCP `simplify_tool` | Optimize for faster checks |
| **Emergency rerouting** | When violations occur | MCP `directions_tool` | Need traffic-aware routing |
| **Daily route optimization** | Once daily | MCP `optimization_tool` | Complex TSP solving |
| **Fleet visualization** | Every 30 seconds | MCP `static_map_image_tool` | Generate monitoring dashboards |

## Performance Benefits

**With this hybrid approach:**
- ✅ Containment checks: ~0.1ms each (instant)
- ✅ No network latency for hot path
- ✅ Still get advanced Mapbox features for planning
- ✅ Scales to 100+ trucks easily

**If you used MCP tools for every check:**
- ❌ 1,500 network requests per minute
- ❌ 10-50ms per check (network + reasoning)
- ❌ Potential rate limiting issues
- ❌ Higher costs

## Zone Update Strategy

Since your zones are likely static or change infrequently:

```javascript
// Update zones periodically (not real-time)
setInterval(async () => {
  // Check if any delivery areas changed
  const updatedZones = await this.refreshDeliveryZones();

  // Simplify new zones for fast containment
  for (const zone of updatedZones) {
    zone.geometry = await mapbox.simplify_tool({
      geometry: zone.geometry,
      tolerance: 0.0001
    });
  }

  this.restrictedZones = updatedZones;
}, 300000); // Every 5 minutes
```

## Summary

**Use this pattern:**
1. **MCP tools for setup** - Create zones with `isochrone_tool`, simplify with `simplify_tool`
2. **Direct Turf.js for real-time checks** - Fast containment without network overhead  
3. **MCP tools for responses** - Route optimization, traffic-aware directions, visualization

This gives you the performance you need for real-time tracking while leveraging Mapbox's advanced routing capabilities where they add value.

You can detect taps on POIs using Mapbox's **Featureset Interactions API**, which is the modern recommended approach for the Standard style. Here's how to implement it:

## SwiftUI Implementation

```swift
import SwiftUI
import MapboxMaps

struct MapView: View {
    @State private var viewport: Viewport = .camera(
        center: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.7749, longitude: -122.4194),
        zoom: 12
    )
    @State private var selectedPOI: String?

    var body: some View {
        Map(viewport: $viewport) {
            // Tap on POI features (coffee shops, restaurants, etc.)
            TapInteraction(.standardPoi) { poi, context in
                // Access POI details
                let name = poi.name ?? "Unknown POI"
                let category = poi.class ?? "Unknown category"

                print("Tapped POI: \(name) (Category: \(category))")

                // Update UI state
                selectedPOI = name

                // Return true to stop event propagation
                return true
            }
        }
        .mapStyle(.standard)
        .overlay(
            // Show selected POI info
            VStack {
                if let selectedPOI = selectedPOI {
                    Text("Selected: \(selectedPOI)")
                        .padding()
                        .background(Color.white)
                        .cornerRadius(8)
                        .shadow(radius: 4)
                }
                Spacer()
            }
            .padding()
        )
    }
}
```

## UIKit Implementation

```swift
import UIKit
import MapboxMaps
import Combine

class MapViewController: UIViewController {
    private var mapView: MapView!
    private var cancelables = Set<AnyCancellable>()
    private var poiInteractionToken: AnyCancellable?

    override func viewDidLoad() {
        super.viewDidLoad()
        setupMap()
        setupPOIInteractions()
    }

    private func setupMap() {
        let options = MapInitOptions(
            cameraOptions: CameraOptions(
                center: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.7749, longitude: -122.4194),
                zoom: 12
            )
        )

        mapView = MapView(frame: view.bounds, mapInitOptions: options)
        mapView.autoresizingMask = [.flexibleWidth, .flexibleHeight]
        view.addSubview(mapView)

        mapView.mapboxMap.loadStyle(.standard)
    }

    private func setupPOIInteractions() {
        // Wait for style to load before adding interactions
        mapView.mapboxMap.onStyleLoaded.observe { [weak self] _ in
            self?.addPOITapInteraction()
        }.store(in: &cancelables)
    }

    private func addPOITapInteraction() {
        poiInteractionToken = mapView.mapboxMap.addInteraction(
            TapInteraction(.standardPoi) { [weak self] poi, context in
                self?.handlePOITap(poi: poi, context: context)
                return true // Stop propagation
            }
        )
    }

    private func handlePOITap(poi: StandardPoiFeature, context: InteractionContext) {
        let name = poi.name ?? "Unknown POI"
        let category = poi.class ?? "Unknown category"
        let coordinate = context.coordinate

        print("Tapped POI: \(name)")
        print("Category: \(category)")
        print("Location: \(coordinate.latitude), \(coordinate.longitude)")

        // Show alert with POI details
        showPOIAlert(name: name, category: category)

        // Optional: Move camera to POI
        mapView.camera.ease(to: CameraOptions(
            center: coordinate,
            zoom: 16
        ), duration: 1.0)
    }

    private func showPOIAlert(name: String, category: String) {
        let alert = UIAlertController(
            title: "POI Selected",
            message: "\(name)\nCategory: \(category)",
            preferredStyle: .alert
        )
        alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: "OK", style: .default))
        present(alert, animated: true)
    }

    deinit {
        // Clean up interactions
        poiInteractionToken?.cancel()
        cancelables.forEach { $0.cancel() }
    }
}
```

## Available POI Properties

The `StandardPoiFeature` provides these properties:

```swift
TapInteraction(.standardPoi) { poi, context in
    // Basic info
    let name = poi.name              // "Starbucks Coffee"
    let category = poi.class         // "food_and_drink"
    let type = poi.type             // "cafe"

    // Additional details (may be nil)
    let maki = poi.maki             // Icon identifier
    let filterRank = poi.filterRank // Display priority

    print("POI: \(name ?? "Unknown")")
    print("Category: \(category ?? "Unknown")")
    print("Type: \(type ?? "Unknown")")

    return true
}
```

## Common POI Categories

The Standard style includes these POI categories:
- `food_and_drink` - Restaurants, cafes, bars
- `shopping` - Stores, malls
- `entertainment` - Theaters, attractions  
- `accommodation` - Hotels
- `transport` - Stations, airports
- `healthcare` - Hospitals, pharmacies
- `education` - Schools, universities
- `finance` - Banks, ATMs

## Filter by POI Category

If you only want specific POI types:

```swift
TapInteraction(.standardPoi) { poi, context in
    // Only handle food & drink POIs
    guard poi.class == "food_and_drink" else {
        return false // Let other interactions handle
    }

    let name = poi.name ?? "Restaurant"
    print("Tapped restaurant: \(name)")

    return true
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Always use Standard style** - Featureset interactions only work with `.standard`
2. **Wait for style load** - Add interactions after the style loads
3. **Clean up tokens** - Cancel interaction tokens when done
4. **Handle nil values** - POI properties may be optional
5. **Return true to stop propagation** - Prevents multiple handlers from firing

This approach gives you typed access to POI data and works seamlessly with the Standard style's built-in POI layer.

Great news! **You'll need to change very little code** because MapLibre and Mapbox GL JS share ~95% API compatibility. Your GeoJSON sources, symbol layers, `fitBounds`, `flyTo`, event handlers, and popups will work **identically** without any changes.

## What You Need to Change (Minimal)

### 1. Package and Imports
```javascript
// Before (MapLibre)
import maplibregl from 'maplibre-gl';
import 'maplibre-gl/dist/maplibre-gl.css';

// After (Mapbox)
import mapboxgl from 'mapbox-gl';
import 'mapbox-gl/dist/mapbox-gl.css';
```

### 2. Add Access Token
```javascript
// Add this line before creating your map
mapboxgl.accessToken = 'pk.your_mapbox_access_token';
```

### 3. Update Style URL
```javascript
// Before (MapLibre)
style: 'https://demotiles.maplibre.org/style.json'

// After (Mapbox) - Use professional Mapbox styles
style: 'mapbox://styles/mapbox/streets-v12'
```

### 4. Replace All `maplibregl` References
```javascript
// Before
const map = new maplibregl.Map({...});
const marker = new maplibregl.Marker();
const popup = new maplibregl.Popup();

// After  
const map = new mapboxgl.Map({...});
const marker = new mapboxgl.Marker();
const popup = new mapboxgl.Popup();
```

